entry.title: picture-in-picture: Ensure observers get OnWidgetBoundsChanged
entry.content:
This CL fixes an issue where VideoOverlayWindowViews (which is a

subclass of views::Widget) overrides OnNativeWidgetMove() but does not

call the superclass implementation. This means that observers never get

a call to OnWidgetBoundsChanged(), since that only gets called in

views::Widget::OnNativeWidgetMove().



In one particular instance of this problem, a permission prompt bubble

did not move with the picture-in-picture window as it moved. This CL

fixes that issue.

entry.title: blink: build fragment tree structure, then notify
entry.content:
When inner/outer html is processed, nodes are created, and inserted

into the DocumentFragment. Insertion is done via

ContainerNode::ParserAppendChild. ParserAppendChild() does the

following (really NotifyNodeInserted and NotifyNodeInsertedInternal):

1. iterates through all the descendants of the parent of the new node

calling insertedInto().

2. calls ChildrenChanged() on the parent of the new node.

3. Notifies any post notification observers of nodes that are

connected.



This means that during fragment creation we may call insertedInto and

childrenchanged multiple times on some of the nodes.



This patch introduces a path that builds the structure first, and

then iterates over the nodes calling insertedinto and childrenchanged.

This avoids the redundant calls (and associated processing).



Bug: 1410020

Low-Coverage-Reason: covered by wpt-tests

(/content/browser/webauth)



This CL removes uses of this deprecated base class by adding a

base::WeakPtrFactory data member.



In some cases, the base class was no longer being used, so it's

simply removed.



In some cases, it was being used as the base class for a supposed

interface class. In those cases, a pure virtual member function

was added so that implementation classes can have a WeakPtrFactory

data member and dispense appropriate WeakPtr instances.

entry.title: Remove usage of NOTIFICATION_NAV_ENTRY_COMMITTED in extensions.
entry.content:
The NotificationService is deprecated and should be removed, but before

we can remove it, we need to remove all of its notifications. This CL

removes one of those in the extensions code.



The CL achieves that by refactoring the NavigationObserver object from a

per-profile "global" object into a TabHelper which is per WebContents.



The change will create a functional difference in that WebContents that

were not tabs in the past and hit the conditions of the

NavigationObserver will no longer do that. After discussing this with

extensions folks, we concluded that it is actually a desired behavior

since it is not clear how well it would work in those scenarios.



Additionally, the CL removes the existing tracking of extensions ids for

which the prompt has already been shown. It was introduced to minimize

prompting for hosted apps, but those are now explicitly excluded from

prompting, so the tracking isn't as necessary. It might actually be

beneficial for each failed navigation to an extension URL when an

extension is disabled to be prompted for, even if the first time the

user dismissed the prompt (maybe even by accident).
